Information synchronization in managed domains ensures user identities, credentials, and group memberships from Entra ID are replicated into the managed domain.

This allows:

* Consistent credentials
* Group policy use
* Legacy compatibility

For example, employees can use cloud identities for domain-joined VMs.

A real-life use case is unified access management.

Another example is cloud-hosted legacy applications.

Synchronization ensures seamless identity continuity.
